<div id="Idea_4037"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaTitle">
<a href="/akira/dtd/4037-4049"><span id="IdeaTitle_4037">Constitutional Amendment: Right to Privacy&nbsp;</span></a>
</div>
<table width=@%">  <tr>    <td valign="top"><div id="IdeaScale_IdeaSubTitle"><b><a href="http://opengov.ideascale.com/akira/pmd/9171-4049">waloug</a></b> <span class="IdeaScale_SecondaryText">1 day ago</span></div></td>    <td align="right" valign="top"></td>  </tr></table>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaContent">A "Privacy Amendment" to the United States Constitution that guarantees a right to privacy in all areas of our lives. This would impact things such as telemarketing calls, medical records access, gun registration, abortion, gay rights and many other areas of personal behavior and activity. Most of these issues were impacted by courts' interpretations of a right to privacy and the debate as to whether the U.S. Constitution has an implied right to privacy as was decided for example in Roe v. Wade. By passing an amendment, this issue and others would be decided once and for all.</div>
<div id="IdeaScale_IdeaFooter"><span style="border-right: 1px solid silver; margin:0 10px 0 0; padding: 0 5px 0 0; color: #666;"><a id="DiscussionTopic_4037" href="javascript:ajaxLink('DiscussionTopicComment_4037', '/akira/discussion.do?mode=comment&dbid=2294&topicID=4037')">Comments (7)</a></span><span id="DiscussionTopicTag_4037"><a href="/akira/ideafactory.do?discussionID=2294">Legal & Policy Challenges</a></span></div><div style="margin-top:3px;" id="DiscussionTopicComment_4037"></div>
